6 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Required display of "in God we trust". (1) The trustees of a school
7 district shall display the national motto of "in God we trust" in each school building and in each classroom of
8 each school in the district.
9 (2) The motto must be displayed on a poster, framed document, or plaque that is a minimum size
10 of 8 inches by 10 inches. The text of the motto, "IN GOD WE TRUST", must be the central focus of the poster,
11 framed document, or plaque and must be printed in a large, easily readable font.
12 (3) A school district is authorized to spend its funds to purchase displays. A school district may
13 accept donated funds to purchase displays and may accept donated displays.
14
15 Section 3. Section 20-7-112, MCA, is amended to read:
16 "20-7-112. Sectarian publications prohibited -- religious materials allowed -- prayer permitted.
17 (1) (a) A publication of a sectarian or denominational character may not be distributed in any school. Instruction
18 may not be given advocating sectarian or denominational doctrines.
19 (b) This subsection (1) does not prohibit:
20 (i) a school library from including the Bible or other religious material having cultural, historical, or
21 educational significance;
22 (ii) the display of the national motto "in God we trust" in each classroom as required by [section 2];
23 (ii) (iii) a pupil from reading from the Bible or other religious material during free reading time; or
24 (iii) (iv) a student from initiating or participating in a conversation about religion, religious beliefs, or
25 religious practices. with another student or a teacher.
26 (c) If a school, class, or course has requirements for self-selected reading, a pupil must be allowed
27 to read from the Bible or other religious material to meet those requirements.
28 (2) Prayer is permitted in a school, on school grounds, and at school-sponsored events, but a
